article.headline: ARKANSAS ST. 53, DENVER 48
article.story:
JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Adrianne Davie scored 19 points to pull
off a last minute 53-48 Sunbelt Conference win for Arkansas State
over Denver on Monday.

Davie was the only double-digit scorer for the Lady Indians
(13-5 overall, 7-1 in the SBC). She also went 3-of-3 in free throws
and was 8-of-15 in field goals. Lyndsay Schlup, Rudy Sims, and
Ashley Anderson each had four assists.

Arkansas State was down by three points at the 23-20 halftime.
With six minutes left in the game, the teams traded one-point leads
and the score was tied at 48 with 1:19 to go. Davie shot two points
on an assist by Schlup and made three free throws in the final 29
seconds to pull out the win.

Tyesha Lowery led Denver (9-7, 4-3) with 12 points and made
2-of-2 free throws. Brooke Meyer added 10 points and made 3-of-10
three-point attempts.
